</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/switch_role\">ARIA: switch role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/tab_role\">ARIA: tab role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/table_role\">ARIA: table role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/tablist_role\">ARIA: tablist role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/tabpanel_role\">ARIA: tabpanel role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/term_role\">ARIA: term role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/textbox_role\">ARIA: textbox role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/timer_role\">ARIA: timer role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/toolbar_role\">ARIA: toolbar role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/tooltip_role\">ARIA: tooltip role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/tree_role\">ARIA: tree role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/treegrid_role\">ARIA: treegrid role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/treeitem_role\">ARIA: treeitem role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/widget_role\">ARIA: widget role</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/window_role\">ARIA: window role</a></li></ol>\n      </details>\n    </li>\n  </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  Accessible Rich Internet Applications (<strong>ARIA</strong>) define ways to make the web more accessible to people with disabilities.\n  This page lists the guides that you can use to help improve the accessibility of web page features such as tables, forms, and keyboard-navigation.\n</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/forms/\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Designing accessible forms</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Learn/Accessibility/WAI-ARIA_basics\">Understanding WAI-ARIA basics</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/Keyboard-navigable_JavaScript_widgets\">Creating keyboard-navigable JavaScript widgets</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Multipart_labels\">Using ARIA for labels with embedded fields inside them</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/practices/keyboard-interface/\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Managing focus in composite widgets</a> (<code>aria-activedescendant</code> vs. roving tabindex)</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/WAI/test-evaluate/\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Testing ARIA</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/tables/\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Displaying accessible tables</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following references are helpful for common accessibility use cases:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Attributes/aria-label\">Labeling widgets</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/landmark_role\">Landmark roles</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/ARIA_Live_Regions\">ARIA live regions</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTML_Drag_and_Drop_API\">HTML Drag and Drop API</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/presentation_role\">ARIA: presentation role</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Accessible Rich Internet Applications (ARIA) define ways to make the web more accessible to people with disabilities.\n  This page lists the guides that you can use to help improve the accessibility of web page features such as tables, forms, and keyboard-navigation.","popularity":0.0034,"modified":"2023-04-12T18:48:43.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/accessibility/aria/aria_guides","github